WEBVTT

00:07.007 --> 00:08.399
What a night, y'all.

00:08.443 --> 00:10.836
I mean,
we snuck out to Belle Isle.

00:10.880 --> 00:14.014
Noah, like, nap-timed
the chaperones with his voice,

00:14.057 --> 00:15.841
and Mildred--
you floated Rev

00:15.885 --> 00:17.191
like a butterfly.[chuckles]

00:17.234 --> 00:18.888
I have never seen
such trippy stuff sober.

00:18.931 --> 00:21.456
You guys are like superheroes.

00:21.499 --> 00:22.848
Like, with your own origin
story and everything.

00:22.892 --> 00:24.024
I guess that makes me

00:24.067 --> 00:25.155
the Kardashian of the group.

00:25.199 --> 00:26.635
Like, bringing a dash

00:26.678 --> 00:28.289
of reality TV fame
to spice things up.

00:28.332 --> 00:30.247
What's a reality TV?

00:30.291 --> 00:31.292
What's a TV?

00:31.335 --> 00:33.381
TV is like radio you watch

00:33.424 --> 00:34.512
like talkies.

00:34.556 --> 00:36.645
And then reality TV is where

00:36.688 --> 00:37.689
you get, like, a bunch
of regular people

00:37.733 --> 00:39.387
with different personalities,

00:39.430 --> 00:41.867
and you film, like,
all the drama that unfolds.

00:41.911 --> 00:44.131
So, like, for example, so,
like, Shanice-- she's our rebel,

00:44.174 --> 00:45.610
so she clashes with Rev,

00:45.654 --> 00:47.351
the golden boy.
And then, Mildred,

00:47.395 --> 00:49.179
you and Hayden are, like,
the "will they, won't they."

00:49.223 --> 00:50.441
Will they, won't they what?

00:53.009 --> 00:54.793
[chuckles]
Just wait.

00:54.837 --> 00:56.099
So, then, what are you?

00:56.143 --> 00:57.405
Obviously, I'm the star.

00:57.448 --> 00:58.841
But nobody knows that

00:58.884 --> 01:00.060
because
I do not have cameras

01:00.103 --> 01:02.105
following me around anymore.

01:02.149 --> 01:04.629
God, I miss being famous.
[scoffs]

01:06.718 --> 01:08.503
Oh, my God, Mariah.

01:08.546 --> 01:10.287
Wh... What?

01:13.116 --> 01:14.596
But how did you
get in here?

01:14.639 --> 01:16.946
Does your father
know you're here?

01:16.989 --> 01:19.427
He wasn't gonna let me, but
I-I really wanted to see you.Okay,

01:19.470 --> 01:20.732
but...

01:20.776 --> 01:22.821
How? How are you here?

01:22.865 --> 01:25.041
Some guy. I-I think he said
his name was Hayden.

01:25.085 --> 01:26.042
He opened the door for me,

01:26.086 --> 01:27.652
and... I don't know.

01:27.696 --> 01:29.306
I guess I just...
I really wanted to meet you.

01:29.350 --> 01:31.961
And I didn't think much past...

01:32.004 --> 01:34.224
Making it happen? [chuckles]Yeah.

01:34.268 --> 01:36.879
Hotheaded runs in the family.Really? [chuckles]

01:38.533 --> 01:40.012
Wow.

01:40.056 --> 01:42.145
[chuckling]

01:42.189 --> 01:43.146
[chuckles]

01:43.190 --> 01:44.191
Oh, come here.

01:45.714 --> 01:47.629
[gasps]

01:48.543 --> 01:50.153
I love you so much, Mom.

01:54.070 --> 01:55.811
[gasps]

01:57.334 --> 01:58.379
What was that?

01:58.422 --> 02:00.555
What?I...

02:00.598 --> 02:02.470
I...

02:02.513 --> 02:04.124
You...

02:04.167 --> 02:06.213
Um, a-are you okay?

02:07.301 --> 02:09.346
Yeah. Yes, I just...

02:09.390 --> 02:10.956
I...

02:11.000 --> 02:13.220
I really need you to know,
t... to tell you

02:13.263 --> 02:14.786
that you were...

02:14.830 --> 02:18.312
You aremy world.

02:18.355 --> 02:20.836
I never would have left you
by choice.

02:20.879 --> 02:22.533
Okay.

02:22.577 --> 02:25.493
But Dad told me
you wrote a letter,

02:25.536 --> 02:27.495
so...No, I never wrote a letter.

02:27.538 --> 02:28.583
I...You never wrote the letter?

02:29.714 --> 02:31.238
Okay, well, okay, I did, but...

02:31.281 --> 02:33.327
So you just lied to me?No.

02:33.370 --> 02:35.067
It's not like that. I'm just...

02:35.111 --> 02:38.680
I'm-I'm just confused,
and I-I saw...

02:40.377 --> 02:43.206
You have this...
this Bridget person,

02:43.250 --> 02:44.903
and-and...Wow. Okay,

02:44.947 --> 02:46.557
what does Bridget have to do
with you leaving?

02:48.907 --> 02:51.345
I don't know
why I thought I could trust you.

02:51.388 --> 02:52.955
This was a mistake.No, M-Mariah.

02:52.998 --> 02:54.391
Wait. Please.

02:54.435 --> 02:56.350
Just...

03:03.270 --> 03:04.880
[protestors
shouting indistinctly]

03:07.622 --> 03:09.841
LADONNA:
This crowd has doubled
since last night.

03:09.885 --> 03:11.669
SHANICE:
I just hope
Mariah got home okay.

03:11.713 --> 03:14.629
But how did your
daughter get in?

03:14.672 --> 03:16.805
She said Hayden let her in.LADONNA: I guess that's why

03:16.848 --> 03:17.806
he didn't go to Belle Isle.

03:18.894 --> 03:20.548
He can see the future.

03:20.591 --> 03:22.245
No big deal.
[chuckles]

03:22.289 --> 03:23.725
Anyway,

03:23.768 --> 03:24.726
your daughter
sounds like a badass.

03:24.769 --> 03:26.075
It's probably not her first time

03:26.118 --> 03:27.381
sneaking back in at dawn.
[chuckles]

03:27.424 --> 03:29.513
ANDRE: Quite the hullabaloo.

03:29.557 --> 03:30.732
And all over us.This is

03:30.775 --> 03:32.603
all good for us, okay?

03:32.647 --> 03:35.650
No publicity is bad publicity
as far as we're concerned.

03:35.693 --> 03:38.218
It keeps us in the public eye
and out of the shadows.

03:38.261 --> 03:39.741
But the government

03:39.784 --> 03:40.916
is a different story.

03:42.396 --> 03:44.920
Steve said they're trying
to have some press event soon.

03:44.963 --> 03:46.704
They want all this to go away

03:46.748 --> 03:49.011
ASAP.You're on a first-name basis
with the guards?

03:49.054 --> 03:50.360
The papers will be here?

03:50.404 --> 03:52.057
Just Steve.

03:52.101 --> 03:53.711
And we don't really do
paper anymore,

03:53.755 --> 03:54.930
but yes, reporters.

03:54.973 --> 03:56.410
You seem an expert on the press.

03:56.453 --> 03:58.194
Being on camera
used to be my job.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.848
On celluloid film?

03:59.891 --> 04:02.807
[chuckles] Well,
it's digital now, but yeah.

04:02.851 --> 04:04.592
I was actually shooting
my own reality show when...

04:04.635 --> 04:06.637
this happened.ANDRE: Perhaps

04:06.681 --> 04:09.249
someone documented the
precise moment you were taken,

04:09.292 --> 04:11.425
then.I don't know.
It's all pretty blurry.

04:11.468 --> 04:14.297
I remember drinking a lot

04:14.341 --> 04:16.430
and then arriving on Belle Isle.

04:16.473 --> 04:18.345
I must have been really trashed.

04:18.388 --> 04:22.087
Um, I was shooting
my premiere episode.

04:22.131 --> 04:23.611
♪ I'm burnin' up,
come put me out ♪

04:23.654 --> 04:25.003
♪ Come and put me out

04:25.047 --> 04:26.266
♪ I'm burnin' up...

04:26.309 --> 04:28.703
This one.Oh, no.

04:28.746 --> 04:30.835
Your body would do nothing
for that dress.

04:30.879 --> 04:32.750
♪ Come put me out,
come and put me out... ♪

04:32.794 --> 04:34.796
[sighs] Have you thought more
about me getting my degree?

04:34.839 --> 04:36.928
I think it could be
kind of good for me.[laughs]

04:36.972 --> 04:39.757
Computer science. What a waste.

04:39.801 --> 04:42.325
You wouldn't even
have time, anyway.Dad thinks I can manage...

04:42.369 --> 04:43.892
Exactly why you know
that's a terrible idea.

04:43.935 --> 04:45.241
Look, being fabulous

04:45.285 --> 04:47.852
is your full-time job now.

04:47.896 --> 04:49.898
Fix your priorities.

04:49.941 --> 04:51.900
And fix your face.
You got a zit coming in.

04:51.943 --> 04:54.076
SHARON: Cut!

04:54.119 --> 04:56.034
[indistinct chatter]That was harsh, Mom.
Even for the cameras.

04:56.078 --> 04:58.994
[sighs] Uh-uh, that wasn't for
the cameras. I meant every word.

04:59.037 --> 05:00.952
You need to think
about your brand,

05:00.996 --> 05:02.040
not your brain.

05:05.261 --> 05:06.958
Hey.

05:07.002 --> 05:09.047
Don't worry about
your mom, okay?

05:09.091 --> 05:10.484
This is about you

05:10.527 --> 05:11.920
coming out
of the ex-wives franchise

05:11.963 --> 05:13.182
with your very own spin-off.

05:13.225 --> 05:16.403
You are our future,
right? Our star.

05:20.624 --> 05:22.452
You know what?
[chuckles softly]

05:22.496 --> 05:24.411
If they're gonna bring in
the press,

05:24.454 --> 05:27.065
I'm gonna make myself
the star this show needs.

05:27.109 --> 05:28.763
KEN: Hey!

05:28.806 --> 05:31.374
No loitering in the hallways.

05:31.418 --> 05:32.462
Get to breakfast.

05:32.506 --> 05:33.681
[mockingly]: Get to breakfast.

05:33.724 --> 05:36.118
[scoffs]

05:36.161 --> 05:38.686
HAYDEN: I wouldn't eat that.

05:44.300 --> 05:46.302
What is that?CORA: A mate in three puzzle.

05:46.346 --> 05:47.651
HAYDEN:
It's a way

05:47.695 --> 05:49.305
to play my favorite game
without a set.

05:49.349 --> 05:52.177
Chess.[squeals] Hayden.

05:52.221 --> 05:53.527
Mildred told me
it's your birthday

05:53.570 --> 05:54.963
tomorrow.
We are gonna party.

05:55.006 --> 05:56.704
How old will you be?[mouths]

05:58.227 --> 06:00.447
91.NOAH: Well, a party

06:00.490 --> 06:02.187
is something to, like,
actually look forward to,

06:02.231 --> 06:03.537
you know? We're
gonna make it sick.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.582
I don't know how or with what,

06:05.626 --> 06:08.455
but, by Gandalf, I'm excited.
[hums]

06:08.498 --> 06:09.934
[chuckles]

06:12.023 --> 06:14.852
Hey, Hay, was I not
supposed to say anything?

06:14.896 --> 06:16.506
Just don't like my birthday.

06:16.550 --> 06:18.465
There was-- I mean, is--

06:18.508 --> 06:21.293
never much to celebrate
when you're locked up.

06:34.002 --> 06:36.004
Your move, bro.

06:37.701 --> 06:39.355
[door opens]

06:39.399 --> 06:41.009
Yo, texpert.

06:41.052 --> 06:43.577
Hey. What's up, J?

06:43.620 --> 06:45.448
Okay, did anybody
pass through here last night

06:45.492 --> 06:47.058
when we were...No.

06:47.102 --> 06:49.017
I checked CCTV
soon as I got your text.

06:50.279 --> 06:51.628
Okay, but then
who drew this?

06:51.672 --> 06:52.760
And when?

06:52.803 --> 06:54.762
No idea.

06:54.805 --> 06:56.503
It's a mystery.

06:56.546 --> 06:58.243
On top of the mystery
of what happened at Belle Isle,

06:58.287 --> 07:00.681
well, twice.

07:00.724 --> 07:02.944
Wait, do you have a theory on
what put us to sleep out there?

07:02.987 --> 07:03.945
Working through
Keisha's body cam footage,

07:03.988 --> 07:05.599
but nothing yet.

07:06.600 --> 07:08.689
I should update her.

07:08.732 --> 07:10.865
It'd give us
a reason to talk.

07:10.908 --> 07:12.083
Hmm.

07:12.127 --> 07:14.042
[indistinct chatter]

07:17.524 --> 07:19.439
[door closes]

07:19.482 --> 07:22.050
KEISHA:
These are for you.

07:26.054 --> 07:27.447
JESSICA:Now that we're all
here, tomorrow,

07:27.490 --> 07:29.492
we're holding a press event

07:29.536 --> 07:31.842
to catch the public up
on the 4,400 situation

07:31.886 --> 07:33.453
and dispel any rumors

07:33.496 --> 07:34.802
that have been swirling
around them.

07:34.845 --> 07:36.499
Carla Coleman

07:36.543 --> 07:37.587
from the mayor's office
will be running the event.

07:37.631 --> 07:39.284
Carla.

07:39.328 --> 07:41.504
Thank you, Agent Tanner.

07:46.378 --> 07:49.381
Thanks to the leak,
which DHS is still working on,

07:49.425 --> 07:51.340
the public knows that
4,400 missing persons

07:51.383 --> 07:52.950
appeared on Belle Isle

07:52.994 --> 07:54.343
and are being detained.

07:54.386 --> 07:55.997
That is all they know.

07:56.040 --> 07:57.520
It's gonna be our job
to remind them of that

07:57.564 --> 07:59.391
by removing any space
for speculation.

07:59.435 --> 08:01.524
In your packets, you will see
approved statements,

08:01.568 --> 08:05.180
the reporters in attendance
and an outline of the event.

08:05.223 --> 08:06.834
Agent Tanner also tells me
a few of you

08:06.877 --> 08:08.183
will be tasked with finding

08:08.226 --> 08:09.924
an ambassador
among the 4,400.

08:09.967 --> 08:12.230
This is going to be key,
as the public needs

08:12.274 --> 08:13.754
to put a face to the situation.

08:13.797 --> 08:16.278
You want me and Jharrel
to find this person?

08:16.321 --> 08:18.585
Okay, look, my job is
to advocate for the residents,

08:18.628 --> 08:21.239
not to play ball
for some government spin job.

08:21.283 --> 08:22.937
None of the family members
have even been notified.

08:22.980 --> 08:25.766
The mayor believes the sooner
the public has answers,

08:25.809 --> 08:27.028
the sooner we can all focus

08:27.071 --> 08:29.117
on returning the 4,400

08:29.160 --> 08:31.554
to society
and moving on with our lives.

08:31.598 --> 08:32.947
JESSICA:
Everybody else, your job

08:32.990 --> 08:34.862
is to get this place cleaned up.

08:34.905 --> 08:36.603
We want the world to see
what a safe

08:36.646 --> 08:39.910
and welcoming environment
we have provided here.

08:39.954 --> 08:41.912
CARLA:
Sorry.

08:41.956 --> 08:43.784
[chuckles softly] I should have
given you a heads-up.

08:43.827 --> 08:45.525
I-I didn't...No, no.

08:45.568 --> 08:46.787
It's all good.

08:47.831 --> 08:49.311
How have you been?

08:49.354 --> 08:51.574
I'm good. And you?

08:51.618 --> 08:53.184
Actually, I was wondering,

08:53.228 --> 08:55.273
is... is Manny...

08:55.317 --> 08:58.015
I-I know the 4,400
are missing persons.No.

08:58.059 --> 09:00.104
Manny's not a 4,400.

09:00.148 --> 09:02.629
Not officially.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.326
What does that mean?

09:05.545 --> 09:07.503
Look at this.

09:10.637 --> 09:12.334
It's Manny's tag.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.729
Look, this appeared
last night.

09:15.772 --> 09:17.121
Only he could
have drawn this.

09:17.165 --> 09:18.296
This is a circle.

09:18.340 --> 09:19.515
No. No, this...

09:19.559 --> 09:20.908
It's his signature.

09:20.951 --> 09:22.474
Look, he draws a circle

09:22.518 --> 09:23.867
and the first number,
and then I come in

09:23.911 --> 09:24.825
with a second number,
and we take turns

09:24.868 --> 09:26.435
until there's 12, but...

09:26.478 --> 09:28.568
Look, I think he's here,

09:28.611 --> 09:29.917
and he's trying to
tell me something.

09:29.960 --> 09:31.658
Okay.

09:31.701 --> 09:34.182
So, Manny came back
with the other 4,400

09:34.225 --> 09:35.966
on Belle Isle,

09:36.010 --> 09:37.620
but instead of telling you
he's back,

09:37.664 --> 09:40.580
he's skulking around,
leaving cryptic drawings?

09:41.668 --> 09:42.669
This isn't like before.

09:42.712 --> 09:44.061
This is exactly like before.

09:44.105 --> 09:46.107
Manny went missing
and you got obsessed.

09:46.150 --> 09:48.326
You followed every lead,

09:48.370 --> 09:50.633
and then you made up leads
when those ran dry.

09:50.677 --> 09:54.202
Spent every night at his place
waiting for him to return.

09:54.245 --> 09:55.812
Never coming home.

09:55.856 --> 09:58.162
Carla, I'm sorry.

09:58.206 --> 10:00.164
All right, I know
I wasn't great

10:00.208 --> 10:02.123
back then, but...

10:03.820 --> 10:05.779
I'm not gonna give up on him.

10:05.822 --> 10:07.476
And wrecking your whole life,

10:07.519 --> 10:10.392
going on these
wild goose chases--

10:10.435 --> 10:11.611
you really think
that's what Manny

10:11.654 --> 10:12.829
would want for you, Jharrel?

10:12.873 --> 10:14.657
I mean,
you already lost one job.

10:14.701 --> 10:16.050
Well, I'm not losing this one.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.096
This job at this hotel

10:19.140 --> 10:20.315
is the only chance I have
of finding him.

10:24.101 --> 10:25.363
Good luck, Jharrel.

10:25.407 --> 10:27.714
[sighs]

10:28.802 --> 10:30.804
[sighs]Hey.

10:30.847 --> 10:34.285
There's my favorite
rebel social worker.

10:34.329 --> 10:38.159
FYI, you'll be doing
a tailored statement

10:38.202 --> 10:39.726
at the event tomorrow.

10:39.769 --> 10:41.771
[chuckles]The public likes social workers.

10:41.815 --> 10:43.817
And if I'd rather
jump off a cliff?

10:45.383 --> 10:47.559
Keisha thinks
you're a bleeding heart,

10:47.603 --> 10:49.779
but I think you just don't know
how to be a team player.Oh, I do.

10:49.823 --> 10:51.128
Just not when the game
is rigged.

10:51.172 --> 10:53.391
Look, I need this job,

10:53.435 --> 10:56.003
but I'm here to advocate,
not to be a puppet.

10:56.046 --> 10:57.526
The game has changed.

10:57.569 --> 10:59.833
If you want in,
here's your speech.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.573
Memorize it.

11:01.617 --> 11:04.098
Play ball, or you're out.

11:16.327 --> 11:17.851
Today, we are
interviewing residents

11:17.894 --> 11:20.592
to be potential
press ambassadors.

11:20.636 --> 11:22.290
JHARREL:
I think

11:22.333 --> 11:23.726
you might actually be great

11:23.770 --> 11:26.686
at the job.
And it could be fun.A job?

11:26.729 --> 11:27.861
Is this a paid position?

11:27.904 --> 11:30.037
No.[laughs]

11:30.080 --> 11:31.865
And how would you rate
your oration skills?

11:31.908 --> 11:33.867
Uh...

11:33.910 --> 11:35.433
Okay.

11:35.477 --> 11:38.436
Gonna take that
as below average.

11:38.480 --> 11:40.221
JHARREL:
So,

11:40.264 --> 11:41.439
how do you feel
about public speaking?

11:42.919 --> 11:44.573
[chuckles]

11:44.616 --> 11:45.835
Me too.

11:45.879 --> 11:47.315
No worries.

11:48.664 --> 11:50.187
What tactics would you use

11:50.231 --> 11:51.449
with an upset reporter?

11:51.493 --> 11:52.494
Michigan Penal Code.

11:52.537 --> 11:55.366
Article three...

11:55.410 --> 11:56.846
twenty-eight.

11:56.890 --> 11:59.022
A person who commits
unlawful imprisonment

11:59.066 --> 12:01.895
is guilty of a
felony punishable

12:01.938 --> 12:04.854
by imprisonment for
not more than 15 years

12:04.898 --> 12:07.422
or a fine
of not more than $20,000.

12:07.465 --> 12:08.989
Or both.

12:09.032 --> 12:10.251
[Claudette laughing]

12:10.294 --> 12:12.427
So, you want me,

12:12.470 --> 12:13.733
a Black woman being held

12:13.776 --> 12:15.256
against her will,

12:15.299 --> 12:16.779
to do all this
work for free?

12:16.823 --> 12:19.347
[laughs]
Fun.

12:19.390 --> 12:21.001
Oh, geez.

12:22.393 --> 12:23.568
Hmm.

12:23.612 --> 12:25.701
Did you have your interview

12:25.745 --> 12:26.833
for the papers?Nope.

12:26.876 --> 12:28.269
Wasn't asked.

12:28.312 --> 12:30.837
Doubt I have
the face they want.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.577
There does seem to be

12:32.621 --> 12:34.014
an air of baloney involved.

12:35.406 --> 12:36.712
But...

12:36.756 --> 12:38.932
when the reporters
are around,

12:38.975 --> 12:41.891
if you get nervous,
remember not to sing.

12:41.935 --> 12:43.937
It would be
extremely dangerous

12:43.980 --> 12:45.503
if your powers
made the front page.

12:45.547 --> 12:47.027
I can't always help it.

12:47.070 --> 12:48.289
Try?

12:50.160 --> 12:52.772
Is everything
all right, Noah?

12:52.815 --> 12:54.861
Where's
your usual joie de vivre?

12:55.992 --> 12:57.689
I-I don't love doctors.

12:57.733 --> 12:59.300
No offense.

12:59.343 --> 13:00.736
Mine haven't been
the most supportive humans

13:00.780 --> 13:02.303
in my life.I see.

13:02.346 --> 13:05.132
Is there anything
I can help you with?

13:08.570 --> 13:10.354
[paper rustles]

13:10.398 --> 13:12.313
I need this medicine.

13:12.356 --> 13:13.531
I haven't

13:13.575 --> 13:14.794
had it in a week.

13:22.976 --> 13:25.282
I'm transgender.

13:25.326 --> 13:26.631
I need this

13:26.675 --> 13:27.981
to be my true self.

13:28.024 --> 13:32.072
Transgender?Yeah.

13:32.115 --> 13:34.988
When I was born,
they said I was a girl,

13:35.031 --> 13:37.904
but clearly, I-I'm not.
[chuckles]

13:38.992 --> 13:41.081
Do you hide this?

13:41.124 --> 13:43.126
It's no secret. I'm proud of it.

13:43.170 --> 13:44.432
I'm out to basically everyone.

13:46.608 --> 13:48.523
Well, this is all...

13:50.655 --> 13:52.875
...remarkable.[chuckles]

13:52.919 --> 13:54.746
Sorry, Doc.
Did I blow your mind? [chuckles]

13:54.790 --> 13:57.010
Well, you've...

13:58.533 --> 14:01.014
...certainly expanded
my vocabulary.

14:01.057 --> 14:02.711
Thank you for sharing.

14:02.754 --> 14:04.844
And you can count on me

14:04.887 --> 14:07.237
to procure
the medicine you need.

14:07.281 --> 14:09.196
Thanks.

14:12.982 --> 14:15.506
It is such a waste that
they're interviewing everyone

14:15.550 --> 14:18.901
for the press thing when there's
only one real option: me.

14:18.945 --> 14:20.598
You wantthis role?
[scoffs]

14:20.642 --> 14:21.991
Then why weren't you
interviewing

14:22.035 --> 14:23.384
with the rest of us?

14:23.427 --> 14:25.212
Well, I'm waiting
for them to finish

14:25.255 --> 14:27.779
and realize they have no one
so that when they truly need me,

14:27.823 --> 14:29.346
their desperation
will give me the leverage

14:29.390 --> 14:31.131
to get the most out of this.

14:31.174 --> 14:33.046
Oh, like get us
out of here?I'm getting my phone back.

14:33.089 --> 14:35.526
[sighs] You know they not
gonna let you say the truth.

14:35.570 --> 14:38.790
How we're being held
against our will.I mean, it's not that bad.

14:38.834 --> 14:40.053
[scoffs]It's not like we're in cages.

14:40.096 --> 14:41.315
Not yet.

14:41.358 --> 14:43.012
LADONNA:
This is my chance

14:43.056 --> 14:45.667
for me to use my superpower:
my media skills.

14:45.710 --> 14:47.582
But use them for what?

14:47.625 --> 14:49.584
CONGREGATION: Amen.Same time tomorrow for prayer.

14:49.627 --> 14:51.803
And for those who haven't heard,
Brother Hayden's

14:51.847 --> 14:54.458
birthday is coming up, and
we'll be having a celebration

14:54.502 --> 14:56.939
in his honor. All are welcome.CLAUDETTE: Looks like

14:56.983 --> 14:58.506
the beginnings of a cult to me.[chuckles]

15:01.291 --> 15:02.727
Claudette.

15:02.771 --> 15:05.078
Glad I caught
you. I could use

15:05.121 --> 15:07.863
your insight
on how to throw a kids' party.

15:07.907 --> 15:10.126
You'd know better than me.

15:10.170 --> 15:12.781
You think that because
I'm a grown woman from my time

15:12.824 --> 15:14.348
that that's
what I'd know best?

15:15.697 --> 15:18.352
Mm.[chuckles]

15:18.395 --> 15:21.224
I didn't mean to offend her.But you did

15:21.268 --> 15:22.530
such a good job at it.

15:29.015 --> 15:31.017
[sighs]

15:37.153 --> 15:39.416
Thought I'd find you here.

15:39.460 --> 15:41.462
Did they audition you, too?

15:43.333 --> 15:45.292
Not yet.They're obviously

15:45.335 --> 15:47.555
gonna use this press event

15:47.598 --> 15:49.078
to screw us over even more.
[chuckles]

15:49.122 --> 15:50.862
Hmm?

15:51.863 --> 15:53.343
But...

15:53.387 --> 15:55.867
something else is on your mind.

15:55.911 --> 15:58.696
We need to get out
of this hotel.

15:58.740 --> 16:00.872
And soon. Noah's not
getting the treatment

16:00.916 --> 16:02.222
he needs,

16:02.265 --> 16:04.354
not to mention what the guard

16:04.398 --> 16:06.008
did to him the other day.
And if they find out

16:06.052 --> 16:07.140
about his voice,

16:07.183 --> 16:10.404
about all the... enhancements...

16:11.492 --> 16:12.972
I think I...

16:14.190 --> 16:17.280
When I hugged Mariah,
I saw something.

16:17.324 --> 16:19.848
I think it was

16:19.891 --> 16:22.111
a memory. Her memory.

16:22.155 --> 16:24.157
Oh.

16:24.200 --> 16:26.028
Oh.

16:26.072 --> 16:27.421
You believe you might
be experiencing

16:27.464 --> 16:29.727
an emergent ability

16:29.771 --> 16:31.555
akin to Noah?I don't know. I...

16:31.599 --> 16:34.428
I wish I wasn't. I don't want
to be afraid to hug her.

16:34.471 --> 16:36.212
Hmm.

16:36.256 --> 16:38.171
I believe

16:38.214 --> 16:41.174
that with patience and study,

16:41.217 --> 16:43.480
we can identify the boundaries

16:43.524 --> 16:45.047
of all these abilities.

16:45.091 --> 16:47.354
That may offer you
a sense of control.

16:47.397 --> 16:49.356
Yeah, but I'll be no better
at being a mom.

16:49.399 --> 16:51.053
I was so rattled

16:51.097 --> 16:54.143
by the vision
and afraid of losing her

16:54.187 --> 16:55.840
that I lied to her face.

16:55.884 --> 16:57.277
Oh.

16:57.320 --> 16:59.061
Well,

16:59.105 --> 17:01.498
we're rarely good at something
without practice.

17:01.542 --> 17:03.674
We're only human, after all.

17:03.718 --> 17:06.503
Go easy on yourself.

17:06.547 --> 17:08.984
And when you see her again,

17:09.028 --> 17:10.899
be honest.

17:12.118 --> 17:14.076
And if she never wants
to see me?

17:14.120 --> 17:15.643
I don't think that will happen.

17:15.686 --> 17:17.601
Your situation is

17:17.645 --> 17:19.690
nontraditional, yes,

17:19.734 --> 17:22.432
but there are many ways
to have family.

17:22.476 --> 17:26.088
It's what you make
of it that counts.

17:26.132 --> 17:28.482
♪ Oh, we're catching
the fireflies ♪

17:28.525 --> 17:30.310
♪ In a bottle

17:30.353 --> 17:32.616
♪ No wait until tomorrow... [knock on door]

17:32.660 --> 17:35.228
Hey, you.
Bridge is bringing home Slows

17:35.271 --> 17:37.012
in, like, five, and, uh,

17:37.056 --> 17:38.666
I get to pick
what we stream tonight.

17:39.797 --> 17:40.885
Okay.

17:40.929 --> 17:43.714
Whoa, whoa. Hold on.

17:43.758 --> 17:46.282
No World War III explosion

17:46.326 --> 17:48.154
about "dad movies"?
What's going on?

17:49.416 --> 17:52.332
You said she wrote a letter,
right?

17:54.073 --> 17:55.683
Right.

17:55.726 --> 17:57.685
I want to read it.

17:57.728 --> 17:59.165
Absolutely not.

18:00.427 --> 18:02.124
It won't help with anything.

18:02.168 --> 18:03.604
And I only told you

18:03.647 --> 18:06.041
about it so that you'd stop
making excuses

18:06.085 --> 18:08.391
for her,
thinking she'd come back.

18:08.435 --> 18:09.784
And she says she never left,

18:09.827 --> 18:11.090
that she was taken. And I

18:11.133 --> 18:12.308
told her she lied
about the letter,

18:12.352 --> 18:13.309
but maybe you were, and...Whoa.

18:13.353 --> 18:15.311
What do you mean,

18:15.355 --> 18:16.965
you told her she was lying?
When did you talk to her?

18:17.008 --> 18:18.227
♪ Don't you believe...

18:18.271 --> 18:19.924
What did you do?

18:19.968 --> 18:21.926
[sighs]
I went to see her

18:21.970 --> 18:24.538
last night.You did what?

18:24.581 --> 18:26.931
You can ground me later.Mariah, what were you thinking?

18:26.975 --> 18:29.151
I knew you'd never take me,
so I-I took myself.

18:29.195 --> 18:31.197
I ca...

18:31.240 --> 18:33.373
♪ Now I'm controlling

18:33.416 --> 18:36.158
♪ The fire restoration...

18:36.202 --> 18:38.029
[exhales]
Well, how'd it go?

18:40.162 --> 18:42.251
Honestly, not great.

18:42.295 --> 18:44.297
I mean, she was nice.

18:44.340 --> 18:46.299
I didn't know

18:46.342 --> 18:48.562
what to call her.
I mean, Bridget is my mom.

18:49.911 --> 18:52.261
I just don't know
what to think anymore.

18:52.305 --> 18:54.437
I need to read that letter.

18:54.481 --> 18:56.178
I need answers.

18:59.921 --> 19:01.836
ANDRE:
I'm not interested in being

19:01.879 --> 19:03.577
your master of ceremonies.
What I need

19:03.620 --> 19:04.795
is medical texts,

19:04.839 --> 19:06.623
contemporary
medical training.

19:06.667 --> 19:08.451
Just yesterday,

19:08.495 --> 19:11.237
young Noah notified me
of a medication I was unaware of

19:11.280 --> 19:13.326
that he lacks access to.

19:13.369 --> 19:14.892
I would very much like your help
in acquiring it.

19:18.983 --> 19:20.289
Well, I will definitely
work on that.

19:20.333 --> 19:22.073
And on getting Noah the meds
he needs.

19:28.819 --> 19:30.604
So?

19:30.647 --> 19:33.084
You find anyone we could use
as our spokesperson?

19:33.128 --> 19:35.348
Anybody willing
and able? Nope.

19:35.391 --> 19:37.785
Myself included.

19:37.828 --> 19:39.961
But maybe... And hear me out.

19:40.004 --> 19:42.093
Mm-hmm.This whole thing
is a terrible idea.

19:48.578 --> 19:50.493
[sighs]

19:50.537 --> 19:53.409
So, who do you have booked
for hair, makeup and wardrobe?

19:53.453 --> 19:56.064
[scoffs] Yeah,
this isn't that kind of thing.

19:56.107 --> 19:57.500
So, you want us to appear

19:57.544 --> 19:59.285
in front of the press
and the public

19:59.328 --> 20:01.722
like the malnourished,
unjustly held detainees we are?

20:03.289 --> 20:05.595
What do you want?I want what you want.

20:05.639 --> 20:06.857
Good press.

20:06.901 --> 20:08.424
And I have
a very particular set

20:08.468 --> 20:10.992
of skills:
memorization, improvisation

20:11.035 --> 20:13.473
and charming... ization.

20:13.516 --> 20:15.649
Look, I'll even sign an NDA.

20:15.692 --> 20:17.651
It's pretty clear you need me

20:17.694 --> 20:19.392
more than I need you.

20:19.435 --> 20:21.655
[sighs]
You'll sign an NDA?

20:21.698 --> 20:22.917
One demand.

20:22.960 --> 20:24.658
I want my phone back.

20:24.701 --> 20:26.268
Your phone?Yeah, you people
confiscated it.

20:26.312 --> 20:28.836
It's pink
with a rhinestone case and...

20:30.664 --> 20:32.622
Wait, did-did you know
I was coming in here?

20:32.666 --> 20:34.537
What do you mean?

20:34.581 --> 20:35.843
My phone.
There it is. Right there.

20:39.063 --> 20:40.413
Right where?

20:43.024 --> 20:46.070
[scoffs]
Look, just get it for me.I can't do that.

20:46.114 --> 20:47.985
Well, then, good luck, sis.Wait.

20:48.029 --> 20:50.901
I can't, but Jessica can.

20:50.945 --> 20:52.686
I'll make the case
to her, okay?

20:52.729 --> 20:54.949
Best I can ask for
is supervised time once a week.

20:54.992 --> 20:56.864
Once a day.Twice a week.

20:56.907 --> 20:58.213
Final offer.

20:59.475 --> 21:01.042
Deal.

21:18.712 --> 21:20.888
So, he stood up,
and I was like, "Oh, my God."

21:20.931 --> 21:22.281
Like, wow. I'm so impressed.

21:22.324 --> 21:24.065
And then I stood up,

21:24.108 --> 21:26.023
and I forgot
I was wearing my Louboutins,

21:26.067 --> 21:27.547
and I kid you not, no lie,

21:27.590 --> 21:29.418
I was, like,
a foot taller than this man.

21:29.462 --> 21:31.246
[women laugh]Like, like, I could fit

21:31.290 --> 21:32.987
one of his Grammys
in between our heads.

21:33.030 --> 21:34.597
Cut![indistinct chatter]

21:36.991 --> 21:39.123
Hi. Excuse me.

21:39.167 --> 21:41.822
I know you're working.
I-I just noticed those...

21:41.865 --> 21:43.476
those lighting
stands and cables

21:43.519 --> 21:45.304
could be tidied up, you know?
Like, someone could trip

21:45.347 --> 21:47.306
and get really hurt, so...

21:47.349 --> 21:49.177
This is my first solo show,
and I really want to avoid

21:49.220 --> 21:50.483
any legal drama.

21:50.526 --> 21:51.962
And also for nobody to die.

21:52.006 --> 21:54.269
So if we could just...[clears throat]

21:54.313 --> 21:55.618
♪ Should've been...

21:55.662 --> 21:57.011
LORETTA:
LaDonna, honey, remember,

21:57.054 --> 21:58.447
you're a butterfly.

21:58.491 --> 22:00.231
Don't bother yourself
with the worker bees.

22:00.275 --> 22:01.668
Now, come away
from the window.

22:01.711 --> 22:03.234
You can't afford
to get any darker.

22:03.278 --> 22:05.062
♪ It should've been us.

22:05.106 --> 22:07.282
♪

22:07.326 --> 22:09.197
Sharon, are we ready to roll?SHARON:
We're ready to roll.

22:09.240 --> 22:11.895
LORETTA:
Okay, let's get this over with.

22:15.159 --> 22:16.900
[sighs]

22:16.944 --> 22:20.295
[scoffs] Can't give a girl
some accessories?

22:20.339 --> 22:23.429
These eyes are not
gonna highlight themselves.

22:28.651 --> 22:30.174
[exhales]

22:38.008 --> 22:39.967
[chuckles softly]

22:50.107 --> 22:52.022
Time to be a butterfly.

22:53.415 --> 22:56.331
They couldn't vacuum
two days ago?

22:57.506 --> 22:59.378
CLAUDETTE:
Well, isn't all this just fine

22:59.421 --> 23:00.422
and dandy for the cameras.

23:00.466 --> 23:02.163
Can you believe LaDonna

23:02.206 --> 23:05.296
is working for the enemy?Oh, let her have this.

23:05.340 --> 23:07.560
[scoffs]She's smarter
than she appears

23:07.603 --> 23:09.518
and more current
than the two of us.

23:09.562 --> 23:10.911
Speak for yourself.
I know enough

23:10.954 --> 23:12.173
to know when I'm
being bamboozled.

23:14.784 --> 23:16.612
Excuse me,
unhand this young man.

23:16.656 --> 23:17.874
Can't. Orders.

23:17.918 --> 23:19.441
Where exactly
are you taking him?

23:19.485 --> 23:20.486
And why don't you take
your hands off him

23:20.529 --> 23:21.922
while you think
of your answer.

23:21.965 --> 23:23.053
They said I have to leave
to get my meds.

23:23.097 --> 23:24.533
ANDRE:
That makes no sense.

23:24.577 --> 23:26.579
Others have been treated
here, so why is he

23:26.622 --> 23:27.754
being singled out?MEDIC: You can take it
up with Agent Tanner.

23:27.797 --> 23:29.625
[Noah humming]It's her request.

23:29.669 --> 23:31.322
Noah.

23:32.498 --> 23:33.368
[humming stops]Remember what we discussed.

23:34.456 --> 23:35.457
We'll see you soon.

23:38.025 --> 23:39.418
SHANICE:They can do anything
they want to us.

23:39.461 --> 23:40.810
CLAUDETTE:
All in the name of good press.

23:40.854 --> 23:42.333
They didn't want the reporters
seeing his face

23:42.377 --> 23:44.031
and forcing them
to explain it.

23:44.074 --> 23:45.728
I should have
protected him.

23:45.772 --> 23:47.034
I should have known
not to trust them.

23:47.077 --> 23:49.471
This wasn't your fault.

23:49.515 --> 23:51.517
We're all doing
the best we can in here

23:51.560 --> 23:52.953
in the face of people
who only want

23:52.996 --> 23:55.564
the best for themselves.Mm.

23:55.608 --> 23:58.262
And LaDonna's about to do
their job for them.

23:58.306 --> 24:00.003
CARLA:
Welcome,

24:00.047 --> 24:02.310
everyone. I'm Carla Coleman
from the mayor's office.

24:02.353 --> 24:04.138
To be clear,
we will not be releasing

24:04.181 --> 24:06.532
any personal information
at this time.

24:06.575 --> 24:08.272
Our goal is to keep
our residents secure

24:08.316 --> 24:09.491
until it is deemed

24:09.535 --> 24:11.188
safe for them
to rejoin society.

24:11.232 --> 24:12.494
Got it?

24:12.538 --> 24:14.627
Good. Okay,

24:14.670 --> 24:16.237
let me introduce you
to our resident,

24:16.280 --> 24:17.891
since I'm sure you'd rather hear
from her than me.

24:17.934 --> 24:19.240
[chuckles]

24:20.633 --> 24:22.548
LADONNA:
Hi, everyone.

24:22.591 --> 24:24.593
I'll be your hostess, LaDonna.
Please follow me.

24:24.637 --> 24:27.596
So, as you can see,

24:27.640 --> 24:30.469
Bois Blanc and the government
know how to treat their guests.

24:30.512 --> 24:33.515
Where are the others?
Are there recreational areas?Of course, but the government

24:33.559 --> 24:35.343
has to respect
everybody's privacy.

24:35.386 --> 24:36.649
I noticed
a fleet of guards on duty.

24:36.692 --> 24:38.172
Aren't
their little outfits cute?

24:38.215 --> 24:39.652
I swear,
I feel like Michelle Obama

24:39.695 --> 24:41.349
with my own Secret Service.[all laugh]

24:41.392 --> 24:42.916
Things have been very scary

24:42.959 --> 24:44.395
and confusing,
but with the government agencies

24:44.439 --> 24:45.875
taking care of us, we have felt

24:45.919 --> 24:47.529
safe and-and cared for.

24:47.573 --> 24:49.313
Uh, Tom Ramirez with the
Detroit Express-Ledger.

24:49.357 --> 24:50.619
You are LaDonna Landry, right?

24:51.838 --> 24:53.927
I-I am. Did you recognize me?

24:53.970 --> 24:56.973
Your mother said that you went
to rehab when you left the set

24:57.017 --> 24:59.585
of your show six years ago.
You look great, like you haven't

24:59.628 --> 25:01.195
aged a day. What's your secret?LADONNA: Tom,

25:01.238 --> 25:02.762
you know the answer.

25:02.805 --> 25:04.198
[chuckles softly]
It is

25:04.241 --> 25:06.200
my amazing 11-step skin care
regimen.

25:06.243 --> 25:08.550
[all laugh]Now I'd like you to hear

25:08.594 --> 25:10.204
from our social worker,
Jharrel Mateo.

25:10.247 --> 25:12.423
Oh. Um...
[clears throat]

25:12.467 --> 25:14.034
Thank you, uh,

25:14.077 --> 25:15.644
LaDonna, and...

25:15.688 --> 25:18.342
friends, for joining us.

25:21.041 --> 25:24.261
Uh, "As a social worker

25:24.305 --> 25:25.828
"for the 4,400,

25:25.872 --> 25:28.701
"I take great pride

25:28.744 --> 25:31.268
"in working alongside
the agencies

25:31.312 --> 25:33.793
to prioritize
our guests' welfare."

25:38.319 --> 25:40.234
Look, this whole thing
is personal to me.

25:40.277 --> 25:42.932
My brother is a missing person,

25:42.976 --> 25:44.281
so I know

25:44.325 --> 25:45.892
how hard it is.

25:45.935 --> 25:48.285
And I hope the day
will come soon

25:48.329 --> 25:51.724
when we are finally allowed
to inform family members

25:51.767 --> 25:54.770
instead of keeping them and
the public at large in the dark

25:54.814 --> 25:57.730
about holding these innocent
people against their will.Thank you, Jharrel.

25:57.773 --> 25:59.470
Always sticking up for us.

25:59.514 --> 26:00.820
Jharrel, can you expand more?

26:00.863 --> 26:02.169
Sorry, Tommy,
but we do have a schedule.

26:02.212 --> 26:04.127
So, we're gonna go
to the dining room next.

26:04.171 --> 26:05.476
Wait until you see the spread.

26:05.520 --> 26:07.130
We have lobster.

26:07.174 --> 26:08.436
[chuckles]
All righty. Right this way.

26:08.479 --> 26:10.177
Looks like you won't have

26:10.220 --> 26:11.961
that unstable
partner much longer.

26:12.005 --> 26:13.223
Mm.

26:19.839 --> 26:21.231
Really, Jharrel?

26:23.103 --> 26:24.321
Look, I don't lie for a living,
all right?

26:24.365 --> 26:25.714
[scoffs]Maybe this whole thing

26:25.758 --> 26:27.455
is a lot easier for you
than it is for me.

26:27.498 --> 26:29.631
Of course you think
this is about being the hero.

26:29.675 --> 26:31.633
You're not the only one
with something to lose here.

26:31.677 --> 26:33.113
If this blows back on the mayor,

26:33.156 --> 26:35.028
it is my head.And I'm sorry.

26:35.071 --> 26:36.769
All right? I didn't mean
to hurt you or your job.

26:36.812 --> 26:38.205
I...Well, you did.

26:38.248 --> 26:39.293
And it still didn't
bring Manny back.

26:39.336 --> 26:40.773
I can fix this.

26:40.816 --> 26:43.340
You don't know how
to fix anything.

26:49.608 --> 26:51.218
[sighs]

26:57.833 --> 26:59.052
JESSICA:
There she is.

26:59.095 --> 27:00.531
The woman of the hour.

27:00.575 --> 27:01.837
[door closes]What can I do for you?

27:01.881 --> 27:02.969
I'm just here for my phone.

27:03.012 --> 27:04.405
I'm sure when people watch,

27:04.448 --> 27:05.667
they're gonna be texting me.
My...

27:05.711 --> 27:06.755
My dad's gonna freak.
[chuckles]

27:06.799 --> 27:09.715
[inhales]
Look,

27:09.758 --> 27:12.195
I have to stick my neck

27:12.239 --> 27:14.154
way out to even get my hands
on it, so...Okay,

27:14.197 --> 27:15.372
that's not what we agreed.

27:15.416 --> 27:16.678
First of all, the phone is mine.

27:16.722 --> 27:18.027
Like, I... Like, I own it.

27:18.071 --> 27:19.028
It became government property

27:19.072 --> 27:20.421
when you came to Belle Isle.

27:20.464 --> 27:21.901
I didn't come, I was taken.Look,

27:21.944 --> 27:23.337
you did a great job today.

27:23.380 --> 27:25.556
It's gonna help your cause.

27:25.600 --> 27:27.733
♪ Because you know

27:27.776 --> 27:30.518
♪ I'm all about that bass,
'bout that bass, no treble ♪

27:30.561 --> 27:32.259
♪ I'm all about that bass

27:32.302 --> 27:33.956
♪ 'Bout that bass, no treble

27:34.000 --> 27:35.697
♪ I'm all about that bass...

27:35.741 --> 27:37.220
Auntie Cha Cha!

27:37.264 --> 27:39.135
You made it!Hey, girl. Come here.

27:39.179 --> 27:40.963
What are you doing here,
Cha Cha?

27:41.007 --> 27:42.965
If I recall, you
weren't invited.

27:43.009 --> 27:45.359
Not by you.
But it's not your party, is it?

27:45.402 --> 27:47.013
Come give your godmother a hug,
girl.

27:47.056 --> 27:48.231
LORETTA:
Stay away from her.

27:48.275 --> 27:50.625
This is her day, not yours.

27:50.669 --> 27:52.192
I don't like your tone.

27:52.235 --> 27:53.672
It's disrespectful.Sharon, what is this?

27:53.715 --> 27:55.848
[indistinct arguing]Uh, this is trailer gold.

27:55.891 --> 27:57.545
Don't worry, if it's good for
the show, it's good for you.

27:57.588 --> 27:58.589
Hon, have a mai tai.

27:58.633 --> 28:00.200
Okay?

28:00.243 --> 28:02.768
Uh, B-cam, are you getting this?

28:02.811 --> 28:04.900
♪ I'm all about that bass

28:04.944 --> 28:06.510
You don't talk to me
like that...♪ 'Bout that bass, no treble

28:06.554 --> 28:09.078
♪ I'm all about that bass,
'bout that bass ♪

28:09.122 --> 28:10.384
♪ No treble.

28:12.952 --> 28:14.388
We'll try again in a few days.

28:14.431 --> 28:16.390
Right.

28:19.045 --> 28:21.743
[sighs]

28:21.787 --> 28:23.658
Where are you, bro?

28:24.746 --> 28:26.052
I miss you.

28:27.053 --> 28:28.707
[sighs]

28:31.144 --> 28:32.232
[knock on door]

28:32.275 --> 28:33.712
What the...?

28:35.844 --> 28:37.411
[exhales]

28:37.454 --> 28:39.195
Carla told me where to find you.

28:39.239 --> 28:40.544
After your

28:40.588 --> 28:41.850
meltdown about
your brother,

28:41.894 --> 28:43.809
she knew you'd be here.

28:43.852 --> 28:46.028
So, this is
Manny's place, huh?

28:46.072 --> 28:47.377
You could've just called.

28:47.421 --> 28:48.727
I know.

28:51.164 --> 28:53.340
You knew you
could get fired

28:53.383 --> 28:56.038
if you tanked the press thing.I...

28:56.082 --> 28:58.040
Well, I can't help you
if you don't care.No, I do care.

28:58.084 --> 28:59.781
All right?
That's why I said what I said.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.565
Really? Because acting out

29:01.609 --> 29:03.306
didn't seem to help
the 4,400 so much

29:03.350 --> 29:04.917
as your own conscience.

29:06.701 --> 29:08.834
All right...
[exhales]

29:08.877 --> 29:11.358
How did you
keep yourself together

29:11.401 --> 29:12.751
after you lost your sister?

29:15.623 --> 29:17.320
My job.

29:17.364 --> 29:19.758
It helped me
focus on something

29:19.801 --> 29:21.063
other than myself.

29:21.107 --> 29:23.457
I think I need that.You do.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.807
Look, you want to be there
for them, be there for them.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.766
They already went
missing once.

29:27.809 --> 29:30.116
It's not fair
they go missing again.

29:33.684 --> 29:34.903
Let go.

29:36.905 --> 29:39.342
Oh, my God.
Is everything okay?

29:39.386 --> 29:40.517
LOGAN:
Excuse me, Officer Taylor

29:40.561 --> 29:41.867
said we'd have some privacy.

29:44.043 --> 29:45.566
[door opens]

29:48.003 --> 29:49.091
The guards seem friendly.

29:49.135 --> 29:50.484
[chuckles]
You know,

29:50.527 --> 29:51.920
we saw the press
piece they ran.

29:53.095 --> 29:54.923
It is ridiculous
how the public's

29:54.967 --> 29:56.359
already eating this up.Yeah, LaDonna
shouldn't have

29:56.403 --> 29:57.839
done that.[Logan clears throat]

29:57.883 --> 30:00.059
Um, hey, listen.

30:00.102 --> 30:01.625
Mariah

30:01.669 --> 30:03.497
has something
she'd like to say to you.

30:03.540 --> 30:06.065
I'll leave her to it.

30:06.108 --> 30:08.328
No. Dad, wait. Don't go.

30:09.416 --> 30:10.678
Yeah?

30:17.990 --> 30:19.774
[paper rustles]

30:19.818 --> 30:21.950
"Dear Logan...

30:23.734 --> 30:26.563
"I'm so sorry,
but I can't do this.

30:26.607 --> 30:29.131
"I tried. I promise I tried,

30:29.175 --> 30:31.830
"but I realize I'm not
meant to be a mother.

30:31.873 --> 30:34.658
"You and Mariah
deserve better than me.

30:34.702 --> 30:36.269
"You have always been my heart,

30:36.312 --> 30:37.444
and I know you will be that
for our child."

30:37.487 --> 30:38.924
[sniffles]

30:38.967 --> 30:40.534
"I meant every vow
that I made

30:40.577 --> 30:41.840
"to you.

30:41.883 --> 30:43.537
"I'm only sorry

30:43.580 --> 30:45.017
"that I'm not strong enough
to keep them.

30:46.714 --> 30:48.324
Shanice."

30:48.368 --> 30:51.110
Mariah.

30:53.982 --> 30:55.288
Logan,

30:55.331 --> 30:57.029
I had no idea
that you would ever read

30:57.072 --> 30:59.118
that letter.

30:59.161 --> 31:01.860
That it would stay with you
for 16 years.

31:04.514 --> 31:06.299
I'm so sorry.

31:07.604 --> 31:11.870
It was a difficult time,
and I-I was scared.

31:11.913 --> 31:14.046
But I'm here now,

31:14.089 --> 31:15.264
and I'd like to start from here.

31:15.308 --> 31:16.875
If you'll let me.

31:18.137 --> 31:20.139
I really hope you will.

31:21.923 --> 31:23.490
[sniffles]

31:37.547 --> 31:38.548
JHARREL:
Hey, Doc.

31:39.549 --> 31:41.769
Brought these medical texts
for you.

31:41.812 --> 31:43.423
Oh, my.

31:43.466 --> 31:45.120
Thank you.

31:45.164 --> 31:47.557
Who is the physician
from whom

31:47.601 --> 31:48.732
you were able to borrow these?

31:48.776 --> 31:50.473
My brother's, Manny.

31:50.517 --> 31:52.519
He wasn't a doctor or anything.

31:52.562 --> 31:55.478
More a polymath,
before he went missing.

31:55.522 --> 31:58.742
I'm... very sorry to hear that.

31:58.786 --> 32:01.223
Might he be among us 4,400?

32:01.267 --> 32:03.008
I had hoped.

32:03.051 --> 32:04.444
Thought I saw a green light
out the window the night

32:04.487 --> 32:05.924
he went missing
and everything, but...

32:05.967 --> 32:08.100
he's not here.

32:08.143 --> 32:09.492
You're sure you want me
to have these?

32:11.016 --> 32:12.365
Yeah.

32:13.670 --> 32:15.629
Yeah.

32:15.672 --> 32:18.066
It's time.

32:18.110 --> 32:20.851
It's right in here.

32:20.895 --> 32:23.158
Um, who are you, again?

32:23.202 --> 32:24.594
Like, am I getting disappeared?

32:24.638 --> 32:25.595
'Cause I just wanted
my phone back.

32:25.639 --> 32:26.945
Oh, no, no, I'm not Gestapo.

32:26.988 --> 32:28.163
I'm Soraya.

32:28.207 --> 32:29.295
I've been trying to get

32:29.338 --> 32:30.861
you alone for a couple days now,

32:30.905 --> 32:33.995
but you were busy, but then...
[stammers]

32:34.039 --> 32:36.606
I found the pilot rough cut
lurking on the deep Internet.

32:36.650 --> 32:38.565
I figured you'd
never seen it and...

32:38.608 --> 32:40.741
Wait, nerd lady, the pilot

32:40.784 --> 32:42.743
to That LaDonna Life?Uh-huh.

32:42.786 --> 32:44.788
Are you saying
you know who I am?Of course.

32:44.832 --> 32:47.008
You're Loretta Landry's
daughter.

32:47.052 --> 32:48.749
I have been watching
you since season five

32:48.792 --> 32:50.229
of Real Ex-Wives of Miami.

32:50.272 --> 32:52.666
I was so excited

32:52.709 --> 32:54.668
for That LaDonna Life
to air, but then

32:54.711 --> 32:57.236
you disappeared
and they said you went to rehab.

32:57.279 --> 32:59.020
I always thought

32:59.064 --> 33:00.630
that you changed your name
and snuck off to MIT

33:00.674 --> 33:03.155
because in season nine,
episode seven of Real-Ex,

33:03.198 --> 33:04.504
you mentioned
computer engineering

33:04.547 --> 33:07.028
and your 4.6 GPA, but...

33:07.072 --> 33:08.595
turns out that you were
just part of an inexplicable

33:08.638 --> 33:10.075
physics-defying phenomenon

33:10.118 --> 33:12.686
with 4,399 others.

33:12.729 --> 33:14.775
You're, like,
my very first stan.

33:14.818 --> 33:16.255
Oh. Honor.

33:16.298 --> 33:17.343
[chuckles]

33:17.386 --> 33:19.562
Check it out.

33:23.740 --> 33:25.699
Ba-bam.

33:27.092 --> 33:28.963
Whoa.

33:30.095 --> 33:31.400
Peace.

33:35.274 --> 33:37.580
NARRATOR:
Not everyone can have this life.

33:37.624 --> 33:39.408
But everyone wants it.

33:39.452 --> 33:41.410
[video fast-forwarding]

33:43.934 --> 33:45.893
[scoffs]

33:45.936 --> 33:48.069
LADONNA:
Auntie Cha Cha, you made it!

33:48.113 --> 33:49.331
CHA CHA:
Baby girl, come here!

33:49.375 --> 33:50.680
LORETTA:
What are you doing?

33:50.724 --> 33:52.639
[video fast-forwarding]

33:55.250 --> 33:56.643
CHA CHA:
I don't like your tone.

33:56.686 --> 33:58.166
It's disrespectful.

33:58.210 --> 34:00.560
And I don't let anyone
disrespect me.

34:00.603 --> 34:01.996
LORETTA:
No, honey, you disrespected
yourself in that outfit.

34:02.040 --> 34:03.041
CHA CHA:
What did you say to me?

34:03.084 --> 34:04.346
LORETTA:
Did I stutter?

34:04.390 --> 34:05.739
Ladonna knows I don't...

34:05.782 --> 34:07.523
Mom.

34:07.567 --> 34:08.655
What are you doing?

34:08.698 --> 34:10.135
You should be thanking me.

34:10.178 --> 34:11.484
For stealing my show?

34:11.527 --> 34:12.789
For giving you one.

34:12.833 --> 34:14.791
You are not enough
on your own.

34:14.835 --> 34:17.185
Reality TV needs
real-life drama,

34:17.229 --> 34:19.361
and Cha Cha and I bring it.

34:19.405 --> 34:20.710
I thought you were smart
enough to know that.

34:20.754 --> 34:22.495
[short laugh]

34:23.887 --> 34:26.238
Oh, honey... you're crying.

34:26.281 --> 34:28.109
♪ That all the boys chase

34:28.153 --> 34:29.415
♪ All the right junk
in all the right... ♪

34:29.458 --> 34:31.330
Good, I'll go get the cameras.

34:31.373 --> 34:33.723
You are unbelievable!

34:33.767 --> 34:35.116
♪ Working that photoshop...

34:35.160 --> 34:36.552
Suit yourself.

34:36.596 --> 34:38.989
Cha Cha,
take three!

34:39.033 --> 34:40.600
No, no, no, no, no, you
don't walk away from me!

34:40.643 --> 34:42.428
You come here, you want
to come crashing parties,

34:42.471 --> 34:44.647
you come and talk to me!

34:44.691 --> 34:46.649
♪ To the top, yeah, my mama...

34:46.693 --> 34:49.348
[sobbing]

34:49.391 --> 34:51.524
[birds cawing]

34:54.004 --> 34:56.050
I asked them to pick these up.

34:56.094 --> 34:58.052
I'll do it myself.

35:00.098 --> 35:01.229
It's my show.

35:01.273 --> 35:03.623
[screaming]

35:05.103 --> 35:08.323
LORETTA: You need to talk
to me first! Hey!

35:08.367 --> 35:10.282
You better take your hand

35:10.325 --> 35:12.545
off of me. The nerve.

35:12.588 --> 35:14.547
Somebody bring me my drink so
I can throw it on this woman...

35:14.590 --> 35:16.549
[crying]

35:18.072 --> 35:20.292
[exhales]

35:23.556 --> 35:26.036
Okay then.

35:26.080 --> 35:28.735
I will bring
the real-life drama.

35:36.308 --> 35:38.048
[indistinct chatter]

35:38.092 --> 35:40.747
How's this?Right there is excellent.

35:43.358 --> 35:45.578
Surprised to see me following
through on my promises?

35:45.621 --> 35:47.232
I am.

35:47.275 --> 35:49.886
My husband was
a preacher like you.

35:49.930 --> 35:51.192
He did things for show.

35:51.236 --> 35:52.367
Or for himself.

35:52.411 --> 35:53.673
Well, that's not me.

35:53.716 --> 35:54.978
But he sounds like my father.

35:56.371 --> 35:58.417
So...

35:58.460 --> 36:00.810
uh, what can I help out with?

36:00.854 --> 36:03.378
Well, actually,
we're just finishing up.

36:03.422 --> 36:05.250
He should be here...

36:05.293 --> 36:07.600
ALL:
Happy birthday!

36:07.643 --> 36:09.297
This is the best we could do.

36:09.341 --> 36:12.213
Can't even find
a light anywhere.

36:12.257 --> 36:13.780
Oh, I, I can help with that.

36:16.696 --> 36:19.351
Look, I get it.
I messed up, but...

36:19.394 --> 36:21.701
at least I can
kind of light this candle.

36:25.357 --> 36:27.272
Wow.Ooh.

36:28.447 --> 36:32.451
It's a very nice light,
thank you.

36:32.494 --> 36:34.844
What're you gonna wish for,
Hayden?

36:34.888 --> 36:36.368
I wish...

36:37.630 --> 36:40.328
I wish Noah was here.

36:41.895 --> 36:44.767
But... but you all
have made this day

36:44.811 --> 36:47.683
better than it should have been.

36:47.727 --> 36:49.250
Thank you.

36:49.294 --> 36:50.469
I mean, there's
a lobster with a candle

36:50.512 --> 36:52.166
in its head. come on.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.951
[laughter]

36:54.995 --> 36:56.910
♪ Yeah, I'm feeling

36:56.953 --> 37:00.827
♪ Like an empire

37:00.870 --> 37:04.004
♪ Whoa-oh-oh-oh-oh

37:04.047 --> 37:05.919
♪ Keep going on...

37:05.962 --> 37:08.400
JESSICA: Yeah, I think that is
the wisest course of action.

37:08.443 --> 37:10.837
Great, thank you.

37:10.880 --> 37:13.274
Bye-bye.

37:13.318 --> 37:15.450
That was the mayor's office.

37:15.494 --> 37:18.148
Apparently Jharrel
keeps his job.

37:18.192 --> 37:20.977
They don't want it
to appear retaliatory.

37:21.021 --> 37:23.241
I can't say that I'm upset.

37:23.284 --> 37:24.633
He shouldn't have said it
when he said it,

37:24.677 --> 37:26.287
but he was only saying
the truth.

37:26.331 --> 37:27.897
God, you're defending him?

37:27.941 --> 37:30.160
He's my partner.But he's not your only partner.

37:30.204 --> 37:31.423
Yeah, well,
my other partner reneged

37:31.466 --> 37:33.076
on a deal I made
with LaDonna.

37:33.120 --> 37:34.382
You couldn't just let her
have some supervised time

37:34.426 --> 37:36.036
with the phone, really?

37:36.079 --> 37:38.299
Do you not understand
the pressure

37:38.343 --> 37:39.866
that I'm under
with these people?

37:39.909 --> 37:42.608
It would be nice if my partner

37:42.651 --> 37:44.740
of six months would be
on my side for once,

37:44.784 --> 37:47.221
instead of the colleague
she met last week.

37:47.265 --> 37:48.614
[chuckles]

37:48.657 --> 37:49.919
Okay, fine.

37:53.575 --> 37:55.316
I'm gonna go back
to my place tonight.

37:55.360 --> 37:56.709
I think
we need some time

37:56.752 --> 37:58.406
to cool off.Really?

38:04.978 --> 38:05.979
Do you like it?

38:07.285 --> 38:09.417
You made me a chess set.

38:09.461 --> 38:11.158
Mm-hmm.

38:11.201 --> 38:14.117
♪ Saying I can,
now it's game time ♪

38:14.161 --> 38:16.729
♪ And I'm always feeling
the same ♪

38:18.861 --> 38:21.299
♪ Like a king, I rise...

38:23.431 --> 38:25.041
You saw that coming, didn't you?

38:25.085 --> 38:26.478
[soft chuckle]

38:26.521 --> 38:28.175
Uh...

38:28.218 --> 38:29.437
hey, Millie?

38:30.960 --> 38:32.832
I think I like birthdays now.

38:32.875 --> 38:34.355
Good.

38:34.399 --> 38:35.835
Want to play chess?

38:37.967 --> 38:41.188
♪ Give it your best,
ain't got nothing on me ♪

38:41.231 --> 38:42.929
♪ Beating my chest...

38:42.972 --> 38:44.800
[knocking][door opens]

38:44.844 --> 38:47.194
So the bad news is I remember
what I was doing

38:47.237 --> 38:49.718
the moment the green light
snatched me up.

38:49.762 --> 38:51.938
I was falling off a roof...

38:51.981 --> 38:53.505
drunk,

38:53.548 --> 38:55.463
shooting my own reality show
and no one

38:55.507 --> 38:57.160
noticed.Oh, my.

38:58.466 --> 39:00.512
And the good?I didn't die?

39:00.555 --> 39:03.341
Oh, and what good news
that is, my dear.

39:03.384 --> 39:05.865
It would be a mighty loss,
a woman of your intellect.

39:07.780 --> 39:09.999
Literally no one has ever said
that to me before.

39:10.043 --> 39:12.045
But you're right, I-I am smart.

39:12.088 --> 39:14.700
[chuckles]
About time somebody noticed.

39:14.743 --> 39:18.530
I see your extraordinary worth,
LaDonna.

39:18.573 --> 39:20.270
Now...

39:20.314 --> 39:22.621
Jharrel loaned me
medical journals.

39:22.664 --> 39:25.928
And perhaps you
could help me refine

39:25.972 --> 39:28.409
my understanding of DNA?

39:28.453 --> 39:29.410
Sure.

39:29.454 --> 39:31.194
All right.

39:31.238 --> 39:32.979
Let's see...

39:33.022 --> 39:34.633
What is this?

39:42.467 --> 39:45.165
Okay, I don't know
what it means,

39:45.208 --> 39:47.515
but it looks like
some old computer language.

39:47.559 --> 39:50.300
My first thought is Cobol, which
no one's used since the '70s.

39:50.344 --> 39:52.433
Well, these books belonged
to Jharrel's brother.

39:52.477 --> 39:54.217
He went missing,
too. Jharrel

39:54.261 --> 39:56.132
also mentioned the
presence of a green light,

39:56.176 --> 39:58.961
but Manny isn't among the 4,400.

39:59.005 --> 40:01.529
It could be nothing.[scoffs]

40:01.573 --> 40:04.619
A missing person,
connected even loosely to us,

40:04.663 --> 40:07.317
with computer codes
from the past lying around?

40:07.361 --> 40:09.363
Sounds like something.

40:09.407 --> 40:12.279
ANDRE:
Could Manny be involved
in our plight some way?

40:12.322 --> 40:13.802
LADONNA:
Or this could lead us to him.

40:13.846 --> 40:15.325
ANDRE:
Seems worth looking into.

40:15.369 --> 40:17.850
We certainly have the time.

40:17.893 --> 40:19.591
♪

40:22.811 --> 40:24.378
[phone vibrates]

40:30.645 --> 40:32.342
PR lady?

40:32.386 --> 40:34.736
Hi, Mariah, I'm Ladonna,
one of the 4,400

40:34.780 --> 40:37.435
here with your mother,
and I need your help.

40:37.478 --> 40:40.699
I've sent you a video
that I need you to put on blast.

40:40.742 --> 40:42.265
To help Shanice.

40:42.309 --> 40:44.224
To help all of us.

40:44.267 --> 40:46.618
Look, I know you're
a bad-ass like your mom.

40:46.661 --> 40:48.707
And I know what people
will do for their moms.

40:48.750 --> 40:50.448
So thank you for doing
the right thing.

40:53.929 --> 40:56.236
I didn't do anything.

40:56.279 --> 40:58.020
I don't know
why this happened to me.

40:58.064 --> 40:59.892
Do you see that?You know what,
I wouldn't eat that.

